         <abstract>
            <p>The multiple exchange algorithm for restricted range approximation is discussed. Efficient formulas are derived for the numerical implementation of the method. Discretization effects are analyzed mathematically. The method is applied to a certain problem arising in digital filter design.</p>
          </abstract>
